parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration during braking can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly, increasing the stopping distance.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels like it "slips" or releases
the vehicle surges forward or accelerates briefly
the brake pedal has to be pressed harder to stop
the vehicle lurches forward
or the braking action momentarily gives out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake malfunction can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle fails to stop or slows down unexpectedly.
symptoms: The brakes feel soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
or the vehicle fails to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable brake behavior can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle's braking action is inconsistent or unreliable.
symptoms: The brakes behave erratically
the vehicle surges forward or slows down unexpectedly
the brake pedal feels like it "slips" or releases
or the braking action is inconsistent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
feels like it's trying to find the right gear
or momentarily accelerates forward when decelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission or clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to shift gears
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
or the vehicle is unable to move forward or reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the sliding doors can cause them to open or close unexpectedly, posing a safety risk to occupants, especially children.
symptoms: The sliding doors open or close on their own
or become stuck in a certain position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
or the vehicle takes longer than usual to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause injury to occupants, damage to the vehicle, and distraction to the driver.
symptoms: The sunroof suddenly shatters or explodes
often without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a spare tire or tire failure can cause the vehicle to become stranded, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The tire pressure monitoring system alerts the driver of a flat tire
or the vehicle is not equipped with a spare tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wind noise and obstructed visibility can cause driver distraction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences excessive wind noise
or the rear entertainment system blocks the view of the rearview mirror.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The instability and unlatching of the third-row seats can cause objects to become projectiles, injure passengers, and distract the driver, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The third-row seats do not stay in the stowed position
lift up when driving over bumps
and can lock into the upright position
causing loud noises and potential injuries. Objects placed on the stowed seats can become projectiles
and passengers can be hit by the seats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The headrest popping off during an accident can cause head and neck injuries, and potentially lead to more severe consequences.
symptoms: The headrest detaches from the seat during an accident
leaving the head and neck unsupported.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Middle Seat Adjustment Mechanism Safety Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The middle seat adjustment mechanism can cause injuries due to the excessive force and speed of the seat movement, potentially leading to closed head injuries or worse.
symptoms: The back of the seat rockets forward with excessive force and speed when adjusting the seat
causing injuries to the head and body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The angle of the third-row seat edge can cause car seats to hang off the edge, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The car seat cannot be securely installed in the outboard third-row positions due to the angle of the seat edge.
